y argues for a new culture of menstruation, one where the joys, rhythms, and controversies of menstrual cycles collides with the defiant, shameless, and bold new possibilities of menstrual resistance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aMenstruationxPublic opinion. 0aMenstruationxSocial aspects. 0aMenstruation. 4aCultural Studies : Body, The. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Feminist. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846214140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438462141423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438462141/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles